{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 8, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "PullRequest", "identifier": ["spring-projects", "spring-boot", 9], "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/pull/9", "semantic_text": "[USER STORY 2\n](https://easibaja06-1741823018668.atlassian.net/browse/FRIENDS-36?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiN2I4MDU2OGFhYTQwNDQ0NTk0NWI3M2EyYzFiOWEyODAiLCJwIjoiaiJ9)\n\nThis pull request introduces several updates across the backend and frontend components of the Kaizen application. The changes primarily focus on adding company update functionality, including adding new endpoints, extending DTOs, updating repositories, and adding new pages to the user interface for managing company data. Additionally, utility functions and routing updates are introduced to support these changes.\n\n## Backend Updates\n\n### Controller Updates\n\n- Added `EditCompany` and `EditUserCompany` endpoints in `CompaniesController`, enabling company updates by ID and authenticated user respectively.\n\n### DTO Updates\n\n- Introduced `CompanyEditDto` to encapsulate editable company properties such as `CompanyName`, `BrandName`, `MaxBenefits`, and address details.\n- Added the `Distrito` property to `CompanyDetailsDto` and `CompanyDto` as these were not included before.  \n\n### Repository Updates\n\n- Updated `CompaniesRepository` and `CompanyDetailsRepository` to handle the new `Distrito` field in database queries and mapping logic.\n- Added `UpdateCompany` method in `CompaniesRepository` to facilitate company updates via SQL commands.\n\n## Frontend Updates\n\n### UI Updates\n\n- Added margins to `companiesList.vue` to be consistent with other tables.\n- Updated `company.vue` and `show.vue` to display company logos and include an \"Edit\" button for navigation to the edit page. Added support for displaying the `Distrito` field.\n\n### Utility Functions\n\n- Added `formatDate.js` for consistent date formatting across the application.\n- Added `isValidUrl.js` to validate URL inputs.\n\n### Routing Updates\n\n- Introduced new routes for editing company data (`company/edit` and `companies/:id/edit`), with role-based access control.\n\n### Miscellaneous\n\n- Updated `Header.vue` to make the logo clickable, linking to the landing page.\n- Removed the \"Edit\" button from the employee list page for simplification.\n", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1610167905.0}
